{"componentChunkName":"component---src-page-post-tsx","path":"/exploring-better-ways-to-write-tests","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Markus Tacker","tagLine":"Software Crafter","description":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at Nordic Semiconductor.‚Äã\n\t\tMentor. Speaker. ‚ÄãConference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê","gitHubUrl":"https://github.com/coderbyheart/coderbyheart.com.git","siteUrl":"https://coderbyheart.com","twitter":"@coderbyheart","defaultCard":"https://images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3Jk4P6nFPNzaz1gsguktk8/350b7e4ddb2c7d86416243d9902920e2/social-card-default-2020.png"}}},"pageContext":{"page":{"id":"e58c9e41-e78f-5668-87d2-54fd0d9a7242","name":"exploring-better-ways-to-write-tests","relativeDirectory":"post","relativePath":"post/exploring-better-ways-to-write-tests.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/57R1fQoWfEuSivwcRPfLUc/3585a62da9ea66ef6b47b6eb09b6bb12/ntd2023-talk.jpeg?w=1300&h=867","alt":"Nordic Testing Days 2023"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"In my talk "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Exploring better ways to write tests"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" that I gave at this year's\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Nordic Testing Days"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://nordictestingdays.eu/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" 2023 in Tallinn, I\ndiscussed my journey from feeling dissatisfied with testing tools to creating my\nown test runner. My goal of this talk was to inspire others to explore and\ncustomize their tools rather than settling for the default options available."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"For quite some time I have been working on cloud-based software system for IoT\ndevices. Initially, I used Gherkin for writing tests, but I encountered\nlimitations in expressing complex scenarios, dependencies, and handling eventual\nconsistency in cloud-based services. Let me explain how I began using Gherkin\nand describe its format and keywords (given, when, then)."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Facing challenges with Gherkin for my specific needs, I ran into issues with\nexpressing dependencies between features, directly embedding JSON in feature\nfiles, managing eventual consistency problems, and dealing with\ncontext-dependent scenarios. I also realized that I needed better documentation\nbeyond just tests. To address these issues, I decided to build my own custom\ntest runner, a process that took me three years to develop. The key improvement\nwas adopting Markdown for better formatting, hierarchical structure, code\nblocks, and comments. I introduced the \"soon\" keyword to handle eventual\nconsistency in tests. Additionally, I utilized GitHub actions to summarize test\nresults in a more user-friendly format."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I also talked about the struggles I faced with architecture diagrams and their\nmaintenance. Auto-generated diagrams fell short, prompting me to explore the\nconcept of using test traces and observability to dynamically generate\narchitecture diagrams based on test runs. This approach would allow for more\nfocused and informative diagrams linked directly to actual usage."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"In conclusion, I encouraged others to create tools tailored to their own needs.\nI believe that developing personalized solutions can significantly enhance\nefficiency and understanding in both testing and development workflows."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"https://www.youtube.com/embed/dZX7SbGOGn4"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.youtube.com/embed/dZX7SbGOGn4","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The slides are available at\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"bit.ly/better-test-tools"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://bit.ly/better-test-tools","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"You can read up about my impression under the hashtag\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"#NTD2023"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://chaos.social/@coderbyheart/tagged/ntd2023","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/5aLkYvjZwohy7T6QM2WeO4/d235090083e5614d8545e6144fb59aaa/ntd2023.jpeg?w=4976&h=3317","alt":"Nordic Testing Days 2023"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"type":"root","data":{"quirksMode":false}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Explori